article.headline: Tennessee Tech 82, E. Kentucky 65
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. -- Kevin Murphy scored 34 points, hit four 3-pointers and went 8 of 8 from the free-throw line to lead Tennessee Tech in an 82-65 win over Eastern Kentucky on Thursday night. Jud Dillard was the only other player in double figures, scoring 14 points for the Golden Eagles (13-8, 5-3 Ohio Valley Conference) and going 8 of 9 from the charity stripe. Tennessee Tech outshot Eastern Kentucky from the line, going 27 of 29 (93.1 percent) to 15 of 19 (78.9 percent). The Golden Eagles opened on a 20-9 run, getting 10 points from Murphy during the spree, and cruised from there. Tennessee Tech led 36-26 at the break and outscored Eastern Kentucky 46-39 in the second half to seal it. Jaron Jones had 23 points to lead the Colonels (12-10, 5-4). Tennessee Tech has won two straight games, as Eastern Kentucky had a streak of consecutive wins snapped.
